quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  18,84,"Verily, We established him firmly in the land, and We gave him a way to everything"
  18,85,And he followed a way
  18,86,"Until when he reached the setting of the sun (furthest West), he found it setting in a black muddy spring and he found thereat a people. We said, \"O Zul´qarneyn! You have authority either to torment these people, or treat them kindly"
  18,87,"Said he, \"As for him who does wrong, I will punish him, then shall he be sent back to his Lord, and He will punish him with an unheard-of torment"
  18,88,"But as for him who believes and acts aright, for him is an excellent reward, and we will give him our easy command"
  18,89,Then he followed another way
  18,90,"Until when he reached the rising of the sun (furthest East), he found it rising upon a people to whom We had given no shelter there from"
  18,91,He left them as they were. And We comprehended fully the forces before him
  18,92,Then he followed still another way
  18,93,"Until when he reached the point between the two mountains, he found below them a people who could scarcely under-stand speech"
  18,94,"They said, \"O Zul´qarneyn! Verily, Yagug and Magug (Gog and Magog) are doing great evil in the land. Shall we then pay you tribute, that you set between us and them a barrier"
  18,95,"He said, \"The power my Lord hath established me in is better than tribute; help me, therefore, with strength (labour), and I will set a barrier between you and them"
  18,96,"Bring me blocks of iron. When they had filled up the space between the two mountain-sides, he said, \"Blow (with your bellows)\". When he had made it red with fire, he said, \"Bring me, that I may pour over it, molten lead"
  18,97,"Thus were they made powerless to scale it, and to tunnel through it"